    "body": "Got a repro:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/117639195/43513fed-2c41-4d4d-8ad0-7bf645e2badb\r\n\r\nWhat I can see\r\n1. Control node: when he creates a community permission, after calling status-go to create a community permission, we parse the response and send a toast notification. Here we see it 1 time only. The state is `TokenPermissionApproved`\r\n2. Privileged member: when creating a community permission, after calling status-go to create a community permission, we parse the response and send a toast notification. The state is `TokenPermissionAdditionPending`. When we receive an update from the control node - we send another notification due to state change (from `TokenPermissionAdditionPending` to `TokenPermissionApproved`), that's why we see an `Update` msg and not `Create`\r\n\r\nWhat can be done:\r\nDo not show notification, that the token was created/updated/deleted by the privileged member until the control node verifies this event. When it verifies it - show the appropriate msg based on the previous state (if it was `TokenPermissionAdditionPending`, we will show that permission `Created` and not `Updated` for the privileged member\r\n\r\nCorner case: The control node processes a few permissions events. In this case on each permission update, we will generate a new msg. This can be handled by sending only one msg (for example, we create 3 permissions and instead sending 3 create msg's, send one for a community), but this is optional",
